[DhtmlXQ_comment0]smg 20130220 02 Xie YeJian W Zheng YiHong||||This was the situation game that was played after 13 rounds when HuNan's Xie YeiJian took on XiaMen's GM Zheng YiHong.[/DhtmlXQ_comment0]
[DhtmlXQ_comment1]In the previous move, black had played C5-1 to prepare to move C5=3 to attack red's 7th file.||Red did not back down but instead advanced his pawn on the 7th file to try to open this file. ||A bold move!||However, this would seem to be rash as black had already been prepared to attack this file. Red could pay a dear price.[/DhtmlXQ_comment1]
[DhtmlXQ_comment8]Red had offered an elephant to try to gain tempo, whereby black accepted heartily.||After a few rounds of play, black has have gained material. ||However, making this move now would seem controversial. ||Black had planned to try to simplify the game as he now had the material advantage by exchanging material. However, althought the strategy was right, the moves played were less than desirable.||Red was thus given a chance to gain tempo and momentum in the attack.||H2+3 might have been better as black would be able to see how red would respond and target his attack with more precision.[/DhtmlXQ_comment8]
[DhtmlXQ_comment14]A rash choice!||Although red's empty left flank was very enticing,  red would still have many moves that could harass black and cause damage.||E3+5 to defend would have been better!  That way, black would not only have defended, the advantage he had with the extra elephant would become a major factor in the game.[/DhtmlXQ_comment14]
[DhtmlXQ_comment16]After much harassment, black's defense finally cracked.||This was not a good move.||Black should have played E3-5. Although he would be inconvenienced for the time being, he would still have a playable game.[/DhtmlXQ_comment16]
